TEXT(&beginproblem);

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;
$showPartialCredit = 0;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 

Suppose \[f(x) = ax+b \] 
where \(a\neq 0\).
Then
$BR

\(f^{-1}(x)=\) 
 \{ ans_rule(10) \}.

EOT

&ANS( multivar_function_cmp( "(x-b)/a", ["x","a","b"],[[0,2],[1,2],[1,2]]));

TEXT(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR $BBOLD Hint:$EBOLD  Your answer will of course depend on \(a\) and \(b\), 
as well as  \(x\).
EOT

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT')); 
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD  Solving \[ax+b = y\] for \(x\) gives
\[x= \frac{y-b}{a}\]
and so
\[f^{-1}(x) = \frac{x-b}{a}.\]
EOT






